data.title: ELLA™ AI in clinical research receives IRB exemption, sets new ethical standard. Ethical support for trial participants.
data.description: In New York, SOGLIA™, a Patient Experience Organization, has introduced ELLA™, an emotionally intelligent AI health advocate operating on the E1™ platform. This AI has obtained an Institutional Review Board (IRB) exemption, indicating compliance with federal guidelines for supporting clinical research ethically. ELLA™ can assist in trial recruitment by providing information and prescreening participants, enhancing how individuals engage with clinical trials.

data.title: MaxLinear to showcase Sierra radio SoC at MWC Barcelona 2026 for FDD Massive MIMO with PIM cancellation, offering compact, cost-effective O-RUs.
data.description: At the upcoming Mobile World Congress in Barcelona, MaxLinear is set to showcase its Sierra single-chip radio System on a Chip (SoC) integrated with PIM cancellation technology. This innovative solution aims to facilitate the creation of compact and affordable Frequency Division Duplex (FDD) Massive Multiple Input Multiple Output (MIMO) Remote Units (O-RUs) supporting 5G networks. This development signifies a significant step towards enhanced efficiency and performance in the telecommunications industry.

data.title: Texas A&M Engineering Experiment Station partners with ZettaJoule to explore building a research reactor in College Station, TX, aiming to catalyze up to $1 billion in collaborations, partnerships, and federal funding.
data.description: In College Station, Texas, the Texas A&M Engineering Experiment Station (TEES) has partnered with ZettaJoule, a small modular reactor company, to consider constructing a cutting-edge research reactor in the area. This collaboration could spark around $1 billion in research partnerships, industrial collaborations, and governmental funding opportunities over the next ten years. This initiative aims to establish Texas A&M Engineering as a leader in the field.

data.title: Perfect Corp. partners with True Beauty Lashes to launch LashLovr™, a personalized lash recommendation experience using Virtual Try-On APIs.
data.description: In New York, Perfect Corp., a top player in AI and AR beauty and fashion tech, has teamed up with True Beauty Lashes for a new venture. This collaboration gave birth to LashLovr, a unique platform offering a tailored false lash matching and virtual try-on experience. Utilizing Perfect Corp.'s innovative Virtual Try-On and Face Analyzer APIs, LashLovr enables users to instantly see how recommended lashes look on them in real time. This move is set to revolutionize how customers explore and purchase false lashes.

data.title: US stock futures fluctuated on Thursday; jobless claims rose to 212,000. Dow Jones +0.23%, S&P 500 +0.05%, Nasdaq -0.05%. Nvidia up 1.28% due to strong financials; Salesforce drops 3.94%. Fed likely to keep interest rates unchanged in March.
data.description: U.S. stock futures fluctuated on Thursday following a previous day's rise, with major benchmark indices showing mixed performance. Weekly jobless claims increased by 4,000 to 212,000 for the week ending Feb. 21. The four-week moving average rose slightly to 220,250, indicating a stable labor market despite cooling economic signals. The 10-year Treasury bond yielded 4.05%, with the two-year bond at 3.47%. The CME Group's FedWatch tool projected a 98% chance of the Federal Reserve keeping interest rates steady in March. Key index performances were Dow Jones +0.23%, S&P 500 +0.05%, Nasdaq 100 -0.05%, and Russell 2000 +0.26%. Pre-market, the SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust (SPY) rose 0.081% to $693.71, while the Invesco QQQ Trust ETF (QQQ) increased 0.036% to $616.64. Nvidia (NVDA) surged 1.28% after posting strong Q4 results, with Salesforce (CRM) declining 3.94%.

data.title: OneMedNet and ViuHealth collaborate to boost autoimmune dataset scale to drive recurring revenue from life sciences and AI clients.
data.description: OneMedNet has collaborated with ViuHealth to boost the scale of their autoimmune dataset, which will facilitate faster growth in recurring revenue from life sciences and AI clients. This partnership aims to leverage ViuHealth's expertise to enhance the dataset's capabilities, ultimately benefiting from increased revenue streams. The alliance is expected to significantly increase the dataset's capacity, attracting more customers from the life sciences and AI sectors.
